MENINGITIS, MENINGOCOCCAL - ITALY: (LOMBARDY) FATAL
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 3 Nov 2017
Source: Corriere della Sera / Milan [in Italian, machine trans., edited]
http://milano.corriere.it/notizie/cronaca/17_novembre_03/bimba-6-anni-muore-meningite-genitori-vanno-prendere-figli-scuola-via-profilassi-6945f800-c077-11e7-8b75-0df914d10fe2.shtml


A six-year-old girl attending primary school on Via Garofani, in Rozzano, died [Thu 2 Nov 2017] night from a form of fulminant meningitis. The death occurred at the Pope John XXIII hospital in Bergamo, the province where the child was on vacation with grandparents for the Ognissanti Bridge. The parents who were accompanying children to school learned the dramatic news [Fri 3 Nov 2017] morning thanks to WhatsApp messages and chats. Panic was triggered: many moms brought the children home immediately. Other parents have stopped teachers and the headmaster to try to figure out how to behave.

After a meeting with Mayor Barbara Agogliati and the school leader Danilo Guido, the leaders of the Health Protection Agency (ATS) decided to immediately start antibiotic prophylaxis for 75 people. First of all family members, including 10-year-old sister, classmates and street cartoon teachers who had direct contact with the girl in the 10 days prior to her death. Then the girls and instructors of the art gymnasium frequented by the little one in Rozzano, in addition to doctors of the nosocomio bergamasco and the staff of Areu who intervened on [Thu 2 Nov 2017] night.

Protect yourself from meningitis with the vaccine: the guidance of the Higher Health Institute

In order to understand which strain of meningitis, however, it is necessary to wait for the results of the bacteriological examinations on samples that have been sent to the Policlinico di Milano. "We have warned those who may have been in direct contact with the child in the past 10 days compared to today. The ATS physician met the parents of the school pupils, providing all the details of the case and explaining that prophylaxis is only for those who have come into contact with the child. "I want to reassure parents that the school is open and there is no risk to children's health," explained Mayor Agogliati.

[Byline: Olivia Manola]

